1 (A) returns home the same day on which the parent or guardian gives the child permission to
2 remain at home;
3 (B) makes provisions for the child to contact the parent or guardian; and
4 (C) makes provisions for any reasonably foreseeable emergency.
5 (2) Except as provided in 16-6-305, a parent or guardian or any person who is 18 years of age or
6 older, whether or not the parent, guardian, or other person is supervising the welfare of the child, commits the
7 offense of endangering the welfare of children if the parent, guardian, or other person knowingly contributes to
8 the delinquency of a child less than:
9 (a) 18 years old by:
10 (i) supplying or encouraging the use of an intoxicating substance by the child; or
11 (ii) assisting, promoting, or encouraging the child to enter a place of prostitution; or
12 (b) 16 years old by assisting, promoting, or encouraging the child to:
13 (i) abandon the child's place of residence without the consent of the child's parents or guardian; or
14 (ii) engage in sexual conduct.
15 (3) A person, whether or not the person is supervising the welfare of a child less than 18 years of
16 age, commits the offense of endangering the welfare of children if the person, in the residence of a child, in a
17 building, structure, conveyance, or outdoor location where a child might reasonably be expected to be present,
18 in a room offered to the public for overnight accommodation, or in any multiple-unit residential building,
19 knowingly:
20 (a) produces or manufactures methamphetamine, fentanyl, heroin, or cocaine or attempts to
21 produce or manufacture methamphetamine, fentanyl, heroin, or cocaine;
22 (b) possesses any material, compound, mixture, or preparation that contains any combination of
23 the items listed in 45-9-107 with intent to manufacture methamphetamine; or
24 (c) causes or permits a child to inhale, be exposed to, have contact with, or ingest
25 methamphetamine, fentanyl, heroin, or cocaine or be exposed to or have contact with methamphetamine,
26 FENTANYL, HEROIN, or COCAINE drug paraphernalia used for the injection, ingestion, or inhalation of
27 methamphetamine, fentanyl, heroin, or cocaine as defined in 45-10-101.
